<paragraph id="8B981015FFADFFFAFF0AFE5706DBFE50" blockId="14.[151,542,439,499]" box="[151,438,474,499]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<figureCitation id="131C0C90FFADFFFAFF0AFE57067BFE50" box="[151,278,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–40" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1866,1889]" captionTargetBox="[175,1408,209,1827]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 27–40. Habitus of species of Penthimia. 27–28. Holotype male P. neoattenuata sp. nov., dorsal and lateral view. 29–30. P.quadrinotata Distant topotypes, color variation; 31–32. Holotype male P.ribhoi sp. nov., dorsal and lateral view.33– 34. Holotype male P.shyadrica sp. nov., dorsal and lateral view.35–36.Holotype male P.spiculata sp. nov., dorsal and lateral view.37–40. P.tumida sp. nov. 37–38. Holotype male, dorsal and lateral view; 39–40. Paratypefemale dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135484/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs 27–28</figureCitation>
, 50, 148–156.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D439EFFADFFFAFF0AFDAF0687FC94" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B981015FFADFFFAFF0AFDAF0499FDFD" blockId="14.[151,1437,546,1075]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Shiny black; posterior margin of pronotum finely edged with orange-brown. Scutellum touched with two lateral spots and one apical spot, yellow. Forewings black with orange-brown spots.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B981015FFADFFFAFF5AFDE704BBFCB0" blockId="14.[151,1437,546,1075]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFF5AFDE70619FD20" box="[199,372,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with rounded caudal margin. Subgenital plate obtusely produced laterally near base, caudal angle rounded, with short hair-like setae. Style with body almost of equal width, preapical lobe well developed, apical apophysis short, thumb-like. Connective with arms shorter than stem. Aedeagus short, stout, dorsal apodeme short and bilobed, preatrium not developed, shaft cylindrical, curved caudo-dorsally with dorsal keel (
<figureCitation id="131C0C90FFADFFFAFF48FD77065EFCB0" box="[213,307,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 148–156" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[242,1352,213,1908]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[194,1397,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 148–156. Penthimia neoattenuata sp. nov. 148. Male pygofer, lateral view; 149. Valve, ventral view; 150. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 151. Style, dorso-lateral view; 152–153. Aedeagus, lateral view; 154. Connective, dorsal view; 155–156.Aedeagus, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135506/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 152</figureCitation>
shown by arrow), gonopore apical on ventral surface, large.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B981015FFADFFFAFF5AFC930687FC94" blockId="14.[151,1437,546,1075]" box="[199,490,798,823]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFF5AFC930671FC94" box="[199,284,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Length.</emphasis>
Male 3.8–4.0mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
