<subSubSection id="C33D439EFFADFFFAFF5AFC0703C2FC01" box="[199,1199,906,931]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B981015FFADFFFAFF5AFC0703C2FC01" blockId="14.[151,1437,546,1075]" box="[199,1199,906,931]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFF5AFC070623FC00" bold="true" box="[199,334,906,931]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name alludes to the similarity of the new species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C276B96FFADFFFAFBBEFC0103C5FC00" box="[1059,1192,908,931]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFBBEFC0103C5FC00" box="[1059,1192,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. attenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D439EFFADFFFAFF5AFC2303C0FB90" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B981015FFADFFFAFF5AFC2303C0FB90" blockId="14.[151,1437,546,1075]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFF5AFC230659FC64" bold="true" box="[199,308,942,967]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
. Both 
<taxonomicName id="4C276B96FFADFFFAFE1FFC22055CFC65" authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[386,561,943,966]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoattenuata">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFE1FFC22055CFC65" box="[386,561,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. neoattenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C276B96FFADFFFAFDF6FC22059FFC65" box="[619,754,943,966]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFDF6FC22059FFC65" box="[619,754,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. attenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble each other in coloration and structure of the male genitalia. However, they differ in the detail of the aedeagal shaft, i.e., in 
<taxonomicName id="4C276B96FFADFFFAFC51FC59031EFC48" authorityName="Shobharani &amp; Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2018" box="[972,1139,980,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoattenuata">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFC51FC59031EFC48" box="[972,1139,980,1003]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P.neoattenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is more slender without subapical lateral flanges except in the 
<typeStatus id="549CAEB7FFADFFFAFDDDFC7A051DFBAC" box="[576,624,1015,1039]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
on one side there is a transverse line as figured. As both species occur in 
<collectingRegion id="49E3DEF7FFADFFFAFF0AFB970673FB90" box="[151,286,1050,1075]" country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Tamil Nadu</collectingRegion>
, Nilgiri Hills some females listed under 
<taxonomicName id="4C276B96FFADFFFAFD7EFB910404FB90" box="[739,873,1051,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Penthimia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata">
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFD7EFB91059CFB90" box="[739,753,1052,1075]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B953CC07FFADFFFAFD62FB910404FB90" box="[767,873,1052,1075]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">attenuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could belong to this species.
</paragraph>
